title: CHOICE_DESCRIPTION
en: Configure what categories of tracking you would like to allow. Consent-O-Matic then fills out consent popups as best as possible based on your preferences. All tracking is rejected by default.
da_s: Konfigurer hvilke tracking-kategorier du gerne vil tillade. Så vil Consent-O-Matic udfylde samtykke-popups så godt den kan baseret på dine valg. Som standard bliver alt tracking afvist.
da_t: Configure which tracking categories you would like to allow. Then Consent-O-Matic will populate consent popups as best it can based on your choices. By default, all tracking is rejected.
de_s: Legen Sie fest, welche Kategorien von Tracking Sie zulassen möchten. Consent-O-Matic füllt dann, basierend auf Ihren Voreinstellungen, die Zustimmungs-Popups so gut wie möglich aus. Standardmäßig wird jegliches Tracking abgelehnt.
de_t: Determine which categories of tracking you want to allow. Consent-O-Matic then fills in the consent pop-ups as best it can based on your preferences. By default, all tracking is rejected.
pt_s: Configure quais categorias de rastreamento você gostaria de permitir. O Consent-O-Matic preenche os pop-ups de consentimento da melhor forma possível com base em suas preferências. Todos os rastreamentos são rejeitados por padrão.
pt_t: Configure which tracking categories you would like to allow. Consent-O-Matic fills in the consent popups as best it can based on your preferences. All traces are rejected by default.

title: RULES_DESCRIPTION
en: Consent-O-Matic comes with a set of rules that tell it how to understand each kind of GDPR consent popup. You can add more sources of rules here - or even create your own list and share it with others!
da_s: Sammen med Consent-O-Matic følger et sæt af regler der beskriver hvordan hver enkelt slags GDPR-samtykke-popup skal behandles. Du kan tilføje flere regel-kilder her - eller oprette din egen liste og dele den med andre!
da_t: Along with Consent-O-Matic comes a set of rules that describe how each type of GDPR consent popup must be treated. You can add more rule sources here - or create your own list and share it with others!
de_s: Consent-O-Matic wird mit einer Reihe von Regeln geliefert, die ihm sagen, wie es jede Art von GDPR-Einwilligungs-Popup verstehen soll. Sie können hier weitere Quellen für Regeln hinzufügen - oder sogar Ihre eigene Liste erstellen und sie mit anderen teilen!
de_t: Consent-O-Matic comes with a set of rules telling it how to understand any type of GDPR consent popup. You can add more sources for rules here - or even create your own list and share it with others!
pt_s: O Consent-O-Matic vem com um conjunto de regras de como entender cada tipo de pop-up de consentimento do GDPR. Você pode adicionar mais regras aqui - ou até mesmo criar sua própria lista e compartilhá-la com outras pessoas!
pt_t: Consent-O-Matic comes with a set of rules on how to understand each type of GDPR consent popup. You can add more rules here - or even create your own list and share it with others!

en: Storage of information or access to information that is already stored on your device - such as advertising identifiers, device identifiers, cookies, and similar technologies.

title: PREFERENCES_DESCRIPTION
en: Allow sites to remember choices you make (such as your user name, language or the region you are located in) and provide enhanced, more personal features. For instance, these cookies can be used to remember your login details, changes you have made to text size, fonts and other parts of web pages that you can customize. They may also be used to provide services you have asked for such as watching a video or commenting on a blog. The information in these cookies is not used to track your browsing activity on other websites.
da_s: Tillad websteder at huske valg, du laver (f.eks. dit brugernavn, sprog eller den region du er placeret i) og giver forbedrede, mere personlige funktioner. For eksempel kan disse cookies bruges til at huske dine loginoplysninger, ændringer, du har lavet til tekststørrelse, skrifttyper og andre dele af websider, som du kan tilpasse. De kan også bruges til at levere tjenester, du har bedt om, f.eks. at se en video eller kommentere på en blog. Oplysningerne i disse cookies bruges ikke til at spore din browsingaktivitet på andre hjemmesider.
da_t: Allow websites to remember choices you make (such as your username, language, or the region you're located in) and provide enhanced, more personalized features. For example, these cookies can be used to remember your login details, changes you have made to text size, fonts and other parts of web pages that you can customize. They may also be used to provide services you have requested, e.g. to watch a video or comment on a blog. The information in these cookies is not used to track your browsing activity on other websites.
de_s: Erlauben Sie es den Websites, sich an die von Ihnen getroffene Wahl zu erinnern (z. B. an Ihren Benutzernamen, Sprache oder die Region, in der Sie sich befinden) und verbesserte, persönlichere Funktionen bereitzustellen. Diese Cookies können zum Beispiel verwendet werden, um Ihre Anmeldedaten, Änderungen an der Textgröße und Schriftarten und anderen Teile der Webseiten, die Sie anpassen können, zu speichern. Sie können auch dazu verwendet werden, um Dienste, die Sie angefordert haben, bereitzustellen, wie z. B. das Ansehen eines Videos oder das Kommentieren in einem Blog. Die Informationen in diesen Cookies werden nicht dazu verwendet, um Ihre Surfaktivitäten auf anderen Websites zu verfolgen.
de_t: Allow websites to remember choices you make (such as your username, language, or the region you are in) and provide enhanced, more personal features. For example, these cookies can be used to remember your login details, changes to text size and fonts and other parts of web pages that you can customise. They can also be used to provide services you have requested, such as B. watching a video or commenting on a blog. The information in these cookies is not used to track your browsing activity on other websites.
pt_s: Permita que os sites lembrem as escolhas que você faz (como seu nome de usuário, idioma ou região em que você está localizado) e forneçam recursos aprimorados e mais personalizados. Por exemplo, esses cookies podem ser usados para lembrar seus detalhes de login, alterações feitas no tamanho do texto, fontes e outros atributos de páginas da web que você pode personalizar. Eles também podem ser usados para fornecer serviços que você solicitou, como assistir a um vídeo ou comentar em um blog. As informações nesses cookies não são usadas para rastrear sua atividade de navegação em outros sites.
pt_t: Allow websites to remember choices you make (such as your username, language, or the region you are located in) and provide enhanced, more personalized features. For example, these cookies may be used to remember your login details, changes made to text size, fonts and other attributes of web pages that you can customize. They can also be used to provide services you have requested, such as watching a video or commenting on a blog. The information in these cookies is not used to track your browsing activity on other websites.

title: PERFORMANCE_DESCRIPTION
en: The collection of information, and combination with previously collected information, to measure, understand, and report, on your usage of the services. This allows websites to count visits and traffic sources so they can measure and improve the performance of the site. It helps them know which pages are the most and least popular, see how visitors move around the site, and where visitors come from.
da_s: Indsamling af oplysninger og kombination med tidligere indsamlede oplysninger, til at måle, forstå og rapporterer på din brug af tjenesterne. Dette gør det muligt for websteder at tælle besøg og trafikkilder, så de kan måle og forbedre ydeevnen på webstedet. Det hjælper dem med at vide, hvilke sider der er mest og mindst populære, se hvordan besøgende bevæger sig rundt på webstedet, og hvor besøgende kommer fra.
da_t: Collection of information and combination with previously collected information to measure, understand and report on your use of the Services. This allows websites to count visits and traffic sources so they can measure and improve website performance. It helps them know which pages are most and least popular, see how visitors move around the site, and where visitors are coming from.
de_s: Die Sammlung von Informationen und die Kombination mit zuvor gesammelten Informationen, um Ihre Nutzung der Dienste zu messen, zu verstehen und darüber zu berichten. Auf diese Weise können Websites Besuche und Quellen zählen, damit sie die Leistung der Website messen und verbessern können. Auf diese Weise erfahren sie, welche Seiten am beliebtesten und am unbeliebtesten sind, wie sich die Besucher auf der Website bewegen und woher sie kommen.
de_t: Collecting information and combining it with previously collected information to measure, understand and report on your use of the Services. This allows websites to count visits and sources so they can measure and improve website performance. This lets them know which pages are the most popular and least popular, how visitors move around the site and where they are coming from.
pt_s: Coleta de informações e combinação com informações coletadas anteriormente para medir, entender e relatar o seu uso dos serviços. Isso permite que os sites contem visitas e origens de tráfego para que possam medir e melhorar o desempenho do site. Isso os ajuda a saber quais páginas são as mais e menos populares, ver como os visitantes navegam pelo site e de onde vêm os visitantes.
pt_t: Collection of information and combination with previously collected information to measure, understand and report on your use of the Services. This allows sites to count visits and traffic sources so they can measure and improve site performance. This helps them know which pages are the most and least popular, see how visitors navigate their site and where visitors are coming from.

title: CONTENT_NAME
de_s: Auswahl, Bereitstellung und Berichterstattung von Inhalten
pt_s: Seleção de conteúdo, entrega e relatórios

title: CONTENT_DESCRIPTION
en: Collection of information, and combination with previously collected information, to select and deliver content for you, and to measure the delivery and effectiveness of such content. This includes using previously collected information about your interests to select content, processing data about what content was shown, how often or how long it was shown, when and where it was shown, and whether you took any action related to the content, including for example clicking on content. The data will be used to personalise content on the website itself, but also in other contexts such as other websites, apps, browsers, and devices.
da_s: Indsamling af oplysninger og kombination med tidligere indsamlede oplysninger, for at vælge og levere indhold til dig og for at måle levering og effektivitet af sådant indhold. Dette inkluderer tidligere indsamlet information om dine interesser for at vælge indhold, behandle data om, hvad indhold der blev vist, hvor ofte eller hvor længe det blev vist, hvornår og hvor det blev vist, og om du tog nogen handling relateret til indholdet, herunder for eksempel at klikke på indhold. Dataene vil blive brugt til at personliggøre indhold på selve hjemmesiden, men også i andre sammenhænge som andre hjemmesider, apps, browsere og enheder.
da_t: Collecting information and combining it with previously collected information to select and deliver content to you and to measure the delivery and effectiveness of such content. This includes previously collected information about your interests to select content, process data about what content was viewed, how often or how long it was viewed, when and where it was viewed, and whether you took any action related to the Content, including, for example, clicking on Content. The data will be used to personalize content on the website itself, but also in other contexts such as other websites, apps, browsers and devices.
de_s: Sammlung von Informationen und Kombination mit zuvor gesammelten Informationen, um Inhalte für Sie auszuwählen und bereitzustellen und um die Bereitstellung und Effektivität dieser Inhalte zu messen. Dies beinhaltet die Verwendung von zuvor gesammelten Informationen über Ihre Interessen zur Auswahl von Inhalten, der Verarbeitung von Daten darüber, welche Inhalte gezeigt wurden, wie häufig oder wie lange diese gezeigt wurden, wann und wo sie gezeigt wurden und ob Sie irgendeine Aktion im Zusammenhang mit den Inhalten durchgeführt haben, z. B. das Anklicken von Inhalten. Die Daten werden dazu verwendet Inhalte auf der Website selbst, aber auch in anderen Kontexten wie anderen Websites, Apps, Browsern und Geräten, zu personalisieren.
de_t: Collection of information and combination with previously collected information to select and deliver content to you and to measure the delivery and effectiveness of that content. This includes using previously collected information about your interests to select content, processing data on what content was shown, how often or for how long it was shown, when and where it was shown and whether you have taken any action in connection with the content, e.g. B. clicking on content. The data is used to personalize content on the website itself, but also in other contexts such as other websites, apps, browsers and devices.
pt_s: Coleta de informações e combinação com informações coletadas anteriormente para selecionar e fornecer conteúdo para você e para medir a entrega e a eficácia de tal conteúdo. Isso inclui o uso de informações coletadas anteriormente sobre seus interesses para selecionar conteúdo, processar dados sobre qual conteúdo foi exibido, com que frequência ou por quanto tempo foi exibido, quando e onde foi exibido e se você realizou alguma ação relacionados ao conteúdo, incluindo, por exemplo, clicar no conteúdo. Os dados serão usados para personalizar o conteúdo do próprio site, mas também em outros contextos, como outros sites, aplicativos, navegadores e dispositivos.
pt_t: Collection of information and combination with previously collected information to select and provide content to you and to measure the delivery and effectiveness of such content. This includes using previously collected information about your interests to select content, process data about what content was displayed, how often or for how long it was displayed, when and where it was displayed, and whether you performed any action related to the content, including, for example, clicking on the content. The data will be used to personalize the content of the website itself, but also in other contexts, such as other websites, applications, browsers and devices.

This includes using previously collected information about your interests to select ads, processing data about what advertisements were shown, how often they were shown, when and where they were shown, and whether you took any action related to the advertisement, including for example clicking an ad or making a purchase. The data will be used to personalise advertising on the website itself, but also in other contexts such as other websites, apps, browsers, and devices.

Google

Google

title: DETECTORS_HELP
en: Detectors are used to determine when a consent popup of this type has appeared on the screen. There can often be multiple detectors for the same popup if different variants exist (bottom bar, middle popup etc)
da_s: Detektorer bruges til at afgøre, hvornår en samtykke-popup af denne type er dukket op på skærmen. Der kan ofte være flere detektorer for den samme popup, hvis der findes forskellige varianter (nederste bjælke, midterste popup osv.)
da_t: Detectors are used to determine when a consent popup of this type has appeared on the screen. There can often be multiple detectors for the same popup if there are different variants (bottom bar, middle popup, etc.)
de_s: Detektoren werden verwendet, um festzustellen, wann ein Popup-Fenster dieser Art auf dem Bildschirm erscheint. Es kann oft mehrere Detektoren für dasselbe Popup geben, wenn verschiedene Varianten existieren (unterer Balken, mittleres Popup usw.)
de_t: Detectors are used to determine when a pop-up window of this type appears on the screen. There can often be multiple detectors for the same popup if different variants exist (bottom bar, middle popup, etc.)
pt_s: Detectores são usados para determinar quando um pop-up de consentimento desse tipo apareceu na tela. Muitas vezes, pode haver vários detectores para o mesmo pop-up se existirem diferentes variantes (barra inferior, pop-up do meio, etc.)
pt_t: Detectors are used to determine when such a consent popup has appeared on the screen. Often there can be multiple detectors for the same popup if there are different variants (bottom bar, middle popup, etc.)

title: METHODS_HELP

da_s: Metoder udføres, når en popup er blevet detekteret af en detektor. De tjener forskellige formål, såsom at åbne og gemme dialogboksen for samtykkekonfiguration.
da_t: Methods are executed when a popup has been detected by a detector. They serve different purposes, such as opening and saving the consent configuration dialog box.
de_s: Methoden werden ausgeführt, wenn ein Popup von einem Detektor erkannt wurde. Sie dienen verschiedenen Zwecken, z. B. Öffnen und Speichern des Konfigurationsdialogs für die Zustimmung.
de_t: Methods are executed when a popup is detected by a detector. They serve different purposes, e.g. B. Open and save the consent configuration dialog.
pt_s: Métodos executados quando um pop-up é identificado por um detector. Eles servem a propósitos diferentes, como abrir e salvar a caixa de diálogo de configuração de consentimento.
pt_t: Methods executed when a popup is identified by a detector. They serve different purposes like opening and saving the consent configuration dialog.

title: WAIT_CSS_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
en: Waits until a css selector is found
da_s: Venter indtil en css-vælger er fundet
da_t: Waits until a css selector is found
de_s: Wartet, bis ein CSS-Selektor gefunden wird
de_t: Waits for a CSS selector to be found
pt_s: Aguarda até que um seletor css seja encontrado
pt_t: Wait until a css selector is found

title: IF_CSS_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
en: True if the css selector can be found, false otherwise
da_s: Sandt, hvis css-vælgeren kan findes, ellers falsk
da_t: True if the css selector can be found, false otherwise
de_s: Wahr, wenn der CSS-Selektor gefunden werden kann, andernfalls falsch
de_t: True if the CSS selector can be found, false otherwise
pt_s: True se o seletor css puder ser encontrado, false caso contrário
pt_t: True if css selector can be found, false otherwise

title: IF_ALLOW_ALL_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
en: True, if the user has all consents allowed, false otherwise
da_s: Sandt, hvis brugeren har alle samtykker tilladt, falsk ellers
da_t: True if the user has all consents allowed, false otherwise
de_s: Wahr, wenn dem Benutzer alle Einwilligungen erlaubt sind, andernfalls falsch
de_t: True if the user is allowed all consents, false otherwise
pt_s: Verdadeiro, se o usuário tiver todos os consentimentos permitidos, falso caso contrário
pt_t: True if user has all allowed consents, false otherwise

title: IF_ALLOW_NONE_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
en: True, if the user has all consents rejected, false otherwise
da_s: Sandt, hvis brugeren har alle samtykker afvist, falsk ellers
da_t: True if the user has all consents declined, false otherwise
de_s: Wahr, wenn dem Benutzer alle Einwilligungen abgelehnt hat, andernfalls false
de_t: True if the user has denied all consents, false otherwise
pt_s: Verdadeiro, se o usuário tiver todos os consentimentos rejeitados, falso caso contrário
pt_t: True if user has all consents rejected, false otherwise

title: FOR_EACH_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
en: Runs an action for each selected element
da_s: Kører en handling for hvert valgte element
da_t: Runs an action for each selected item
de_s: Führt eine Aktion für jedes ausgewählte Element aus
de_t: Performs an action on each selected item
pt_s: Executa uma ação para cada elemento selecionado
pt_t: Performs an action for each selected element

title: SLIDE_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
de_s: Simuliert die Interaktion mit einem Schieberegler
pt_s: Simula a interação com um controle deslizante

title: HIDE_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
en: Hides the element found with the given css selector.
da_s: Skjuler elementet fundet med den givne css-vælger.
da_t: Hides the element found with the given css selector.
de_s: Blendet das Element aus, das mit dem angegebenen CSS-Selektor gefunden wurde.
de_t: Hides the element found with the specified CSS selector.
pt_s: Oculta o elemento encontrado com o seletor css fornecido.
pt_t: Hides the element found with the given css selector.

title: WAIT_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
en: Waits a given amount of time before continuing
da_s: Venter et givet stykke tid, før der fortsættes
da_t: Waits a certain amount of time before continuing
de_s: Wartet eine bestimmte Zeit, bevor fortgefahren wird
de_t: Waits a specified amount of time before continuing
pt_s: Aguarda um determinado período de tempo antes de continuar
pt_t: Wait a certain amount of time before continuing

title: CONSENT_DESCRIPTION
en: Used to handle consent, inside a ConsentAction
da_s: Bruges til at håndtere samtykke inde i en ConsentHandling
da_t: Used to handle consent inside a ConsentHandling
de_s: Wird verwendet, um die Zustimmung innerhalb einer ConsentAction zu verarbeiten
de_t: Used to process consent within a ConsentAction
pt_s: Usado para lidar com o consentimento, dentro de um ConsentAction
pt_t: Used to handle consent, inside a ConsentAction

title: HIDE_FROM_DETECTION_HELP
en: Make sure this element and its children, is never detected by ConsentOMatic
da_s: Sørg for, at dette element og dets børn aldrig bliver opdaget af ConsentOMatic
da_t: Ensure that this element and its children are never detected by ConsentOMatic
de_s: Stellen Sie sicher, dass dieses Element und seine untergeordneten Elemente niemals von ConsentOMatic erkannt werden
de_t: Ensure that this element and its children are never recognized by ConsentOMatic
pt_s: Certifique-se de que este elemento e seus filhos nunca sejam detectados pelo ConsentOMatic
pt_t: Make sure this element and its children are never detected by ConsentOMatic

title: FORCE_HIDE_HELP
en: Force hiding this element, instead of using picture in picture
da_s: Tving at dette element bliver skjult i stedet for at bruge billede i billede
da_t: Force this element to be hidden instead of using picture in picture
de_s: Erzwingen Sie das Ausblenden dieses Elements, anstatt Bild in Bild zu verwenden
de_t: Force hide this element instead of using picture in picture
pt_s: Forçar a ocultação deste elemento, em vez de usar imagem em imagem
pt_t: Force hide this element instead of using picture in picture

title: NEGATED_CHECKBOX_HELP
en: If checked, the checkbox count as checked when not checked, and vice versa
da_s: Hvis markeret, tæller afkrydsningsfeltet som markeret, når det ikke er markeret, og omvendt
da_t: If checked, the checkbox counts as checked when unchecked, and vice versa
de_s: Wenn es aktiviert ist, zählt das Kontrollkästchen als aktiviert, wenn es nicht aktiviert ist, und umgekehrt
de_t: If checked, the checkbox counts as checked, if not checked, and vice versa
pt_s: Se marcada, a caixa de seleção conta como marcada quando não marcada e vice-versa
pt_t: If checked, the checkbox counts as checked when unchecked and vice versa

title: RUN_ROOTED_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
en: Run an action rooted at the selected dom element. Ignores any current root set, and sets old root afterwards.

title: IGNORE_OLD_ROOT_HELP
en: Ignores any root set, and restarts from document

title: NEGATED_URL_HELP
en: When enabled, this matcher matches, if none of the URL's match
